{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|みお}}

{{IPAfont|⟨mi<sub>1</sub> wo⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/mʲiwo/}} → {{IPAchar|/miwo/}} → {{IPAchar|/mio/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=みお}}, first attested in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' (''c.'' 759 {{CE}}).<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|7|1108}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man7Yos.html#1108 here]</ref>

Derived as a compound of {{com|ja|sort=みお|水|tr1=mi|t1=[[water]]|pos1=ancient combining form|緒|tr2=wo → o|t2=[[cord]]; something [[long]] and [[continue|continuing]]|pos2=likely cognate with {{m|ja|尾|tr=o||[[tail]]}} from the sense of “something long and continuing from the [[end]] of the [[main]] [[body]]”}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

{{ja-noun|みお|hhira=みを}}

